title: NYC House Incumbents Coast to Victory, as Other Races Hang in Balance
description: Several races, including one involving Representative Sean Patrick Maloney, the powerful Democratic leader, were still awaiting further vote counts.
dc:creator: Michael Gold
media:credit: Jose A. Alvarado Jr. for The New York Times
media:description: Nicole Malliotakis defended her seat in the 11th Congressional District against Max Rose, a Democrat whom she unseated two years ago.
